Stage 4 Architectural Invariants (Frozen)

1. Failure Boundary (Detection ↔ Result Plane)

Rule: Failure in Result Plane does not propagate upstream.

Implication:

If ResultConsumer dies, Detection MUST NOT crash, stall, or buffer.

Detection fires messages to the Bus and forgets them (Fire-and-Forget).

Detection must never depend on Result Plane liveness.

2. Infrastructure Status (The Bus)

Status: DEV-ONLY COMPONENT.

Definition: SimpleBus (infrastructure/bus.py) is a development convenience tool, not a production message broker.

Roadmap: It is explicitly scheduled to be replaced completely in Stage 5.

Prohibition: Do not build reliability, persistence, or ordering logic on top of SimpleBus.

